Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"58b45fa8-879e-4159-9f4b-7a106cf747d9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Exploratory ",
 StyleBox["analysis",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}]
}], "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112494180145884`*^9, 
  3.8112494194302664`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fa2a98d1-41ec-457f-ba1e-\
e077687ad4e5"],

Cell["\<\
An approach to analysing data sets to find previously unknown relationships\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112494273317204`*^9, 3.8112494366601334`*^9}, 
   3.979034046668501*^9},ExpressionUUID->"3ca298c6-00d6-4a3a-8353-\
d8545cd1891e"],

Cell["Often involves visualization techniques", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112494273317204`*^9, 
  3.811249440404746*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"82aed0b1-b4f1-4391-afe4-\
aa8c5c57fe96"],

Cell["Useful when we lack a clear question or a hypothesis", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8112494273317204`*^9, 
  3.811249439967704*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"60661bf7-a826-4477-9802-\
673435aaa47b"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"b61dce16-765f-4c39-b867-9ab9bc86495e"],

Cell["Descriptive analysis : variables", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811246721085638*^9, 
  3.8112467329145308`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c909f8db-2880-4f4c-90f6-\
55544df6d26e"],

Cell["\<\
The first kind of analysis performed on a dataset is to represent it by \
variables. Understanding the type of a variable is relevant to determine the \
analysis to be done on the data. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811246749373634*^9, 3.8112468076544867`*^9}, {
   3.811248285531762*^9, 3.811248288834229*^9}, 3.813240050103554*^9, {
   3.88597406110629*^9, 3.8859741342117577`*^9}, {3.885974185003841*^9, 
   3.88597419791669*^9}, {3.887276985789316*^9, 3.887277005735224*^9}, {
   3.887277052325494*^9, 3.887277054308074*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"5ef4decc-aee9-4ec5-8f95-858343beca04"],

Cell["\<\

 Variables can be :\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811246749373634*^9, 3.8112468076544867`*^9}, {
   3.811248285531762*^9, 3.811248288834229*^9}, 3.813240062014112*^9, {
   3.854869304369582*^9, 3.854869326980373*^9}, {3.885972227972899*^9, 
   3.885972232628831*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fd50b0e2-7aca-41d9-97aa-\
370d29c41294"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Categorical or discrete: represent values that can be sorted/classified into \
2 or more groups/categories. There are two types of categorical variable: \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.885972244884273*^9, 3.88597227418886*^9}, {
  3.885972335095727*^9, 3.885972338417391*^9}, {3.88597239006981*^9, 
  3.885972461319776*^9}, {3.885972494494391*^9, 3.8859725278231583`*^9}, {
  3.885972754671833*^9, 3.885972779294511*^9}, {3.885972913336139*^9, 
  3.885972922016657*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6bef7745-528b-4cbd-963b-\
e57a524fab41"],

Cell["\<\
Nominal : it has no intrinsic ordering or ranking to its categories. They can \
be coded by numbers. Example: gender, race, post code, blood type.\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.885972244884273*^9, 3.88597227418886*^9}, {
  3.885972335095727*^9, 3.885972338417391*^9}, {3.88597239006981*^9, 
  3.885972460270334*^9}, {3.885972500016341*^9, 3.885972547423266*^9}, {
  3.8859726127741337`*^9, 3.8859726371015244`*^9}, {3.885972736854795*^9, 
  3.88597274850375*^9}, {3.885972933494457*^9, 
  3.885972933509247*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1ab94394-b3bd-4a63-93e0-\
e31b8d612e7f"],

Cell["\<\
Ordinal: categories can ordered/ranked. Example: Olympic medals (gold, \
silver, bronze), socio economic status (low, middle or high income), \
education level, satisfaction rating (\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]extremely \
dislike\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]dislike\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]neutral\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]satisfied\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote], \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]very satisfied\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]).\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.885972244884273*^9, 3.88597227418886*^9}, {
   3.885972335095727*^9, 3.885972338417391*^9}, {3.88597239006981*^9, 
   3.885972460270334*^9}, {3.885972500016341*^9, 3.885972547423266*^9}, {
   3.8859726127741337`*^9, 3.8859726371015244`*^9}, {3.885972736854795*^9, 
   3.88597274850375*^9}, {3.885972934361553*^9, 3.885973011241568*^9}, 
   3.885973057536374*^9, {3.88597308824066*^9, 3.88597314823939*^9}, {
   3.885973190677408*^9, 
   3.885973190690633*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"edcc6352-b0cb-4cbd-a749-\
39aa4fa92247"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Numerical or continuous variables: represent values that belong to the Real \
set of numbers. There are two types of numerical variables:\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.885972244884273*^9, 3.88597227418886*^9}, {
  3.885972335095727*^9, 3.885972338417391*^9}, {3.88597239006981*^9, 
  3.885972461319776*^9}, {3.885972494494391*^9, 3.8859725278231583`*^9}, {
  3.885972754671833*^9, 3.885972779294511*^9}, {3.885972913336139*^9, 
  3.885972922016657*^9}, {3.885973236048418*^9, 3.885973253993391*^9}, {
  3.885973333290126*^9, 
  3.885973402102213*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e735818d-59dc-4729-b0b5-\
f76b2ae5c036"],

Cell[TextData[{
 " interval: it represent values whose differences have meaning, but it does \
not have a true zero:  temperature in Centigrade degrees. Water boils at \
100",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["\[Null]", 
          StyleBox["o", "TI"]], 
         StyleBox["C", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "$^oC$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "068ead3b-071f-4de7-9322-8e6e45316fd9"],
 ", and it is liquid within [0",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["\[Null]", 
          StyleBox["o", "TI"]], 
         StyleBox["C", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "$^oC$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8dbe5ea7-bd03-4b87-94fc-65f122798127"],
 ", 100",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["\[Null]", 
          StyleBox["o", "TI"]], 
         StyleBox["C", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "$^oC$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e1143d64-ad3a-4e08-a6dd-bbd2ce39f9be"],
 "], but at 0",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["\[Null]", 
          StyleBox["o", "TI"]], 
         StyleBox["C", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "$^oC$", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "22d28d18-07cf-4ba6-b75d-f3390c699279"],
 " there is still water. "
}], "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.885972244884273*^9, 3.88597227418886*^9}, {
   3.885972335095727*^9, 3.885972338417391*^9}, {3.88597239006981*^9, 
   3.885972461319776*^9}, {3.885972494494391*^9, 3.8859725278231583`*^9}, {
   3.885972754671833*^9, 3.885972779294511*^9}, {3.885972913336139*^9, 
   3.885972922016657*^9}, {3.885973236048418*^9, 3.885973253993391*^9}, {
   3.885973333290126*^9, 3.885973412632585*^9}, {3.885973612639054*^9, 
   3.885973664989146*^9}, {3.885973695814138*^9, 3.8859736997793827`*^9}, {
   3.885973815198975*^9, 3.885973962066226*^9}, 3.906806955929864*^9, {
   3.9179495869912233`*^9, 
   3.917949587423967*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"17a3ea1a-40d9-4a28-913e-\
d052351b0342"],

Cell["\<\
ratio: has a true meaning for zero, and all mathematical operations can be \
applied to it. Example: dose amount, flow rate, concentration, pulse, weight \
(0Kg means there is nothing of that), length, temperature in Kelvin (0.0 \
Kelvin really does mean \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]no \
heat\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]). \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.885972244884273*^9, 3.88597227418886*^9}, {
  3.885972335095727*^9, 3.885972338417391*^9}, {3.88597239006981*^9, 
  3.885972461319776*^9}, {3.885972494494391*^9, 3.8859725278231583`*^9}, {
  3.885972754671833*^9, 3.885972779294511*^9}, {3.885972913336139*^9, 
  3.885972922016657*^9}, {3.885973236048418*^9, 3.885973253993391*^9}, {
  3.885973333290126*^9, 3.885973422334765*^9}, {3.885973974810322*^9, 
  3.885973981074011*^9}, {3.8859740132645884`*^9, 3.885974046704443*^9}, {
  3.8859742336632767`*^9, 
  3.885974310035907*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b1db6afd-5108-4897-ab4e-\
a1d2831820e4"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
When working with all types of variables in a model, we can classify the \
variables as:\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8859734313625307`*^9, 
  3.8859734463080063`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6ab3911a-f179-4594-a5c4-\
0673cda63f26"],

Cell["\<\
independent: not influenced by others, also called predictor variable\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811246749373634*^9, 
  3.811246903474512*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"585366d0-ac55-42e0-abcf-\
112d8fd39fe2"],

Cell["\<\
dependent: depends on other variables. It can be used to predict variable \
that depends on. 
\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811246749373634*^9, 3.811246926888931*^9}, {
  3.885973478916134*^9, 
  3.885973497474498*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9a6569db-a161-49c1-90f3-\
f3ce887e8d12"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell["\<\
This initial variable versus values identification is followed by descriptive \
statistics, that quantitatively describes or summarises features of a dataset\
\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811246933230196*^9, 3.8112469965489383`*^9}},
 FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"9dd89b1a-747f-468f-992e-b63a9b8315d2"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
