Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"d4fc2dee-3fe2-4a26-9948-83aa440066e5"],

Cell["Outlier detection, by measures of locality", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7770957305258493`*^9, 3.777095735638084*^9}, 
   3.777096012246889*^9, {3.811247144371107*^9, 3.811247145796303*^9}, {
   3.8112481251868124`*^9, 
   3.811248128704361*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"80fe7ee6-bdac-40f3-ae9a-\
c798623c531e"],

Cell["\<\
In several cases, an outlier or extreme case is not the result of bad data, \
and often can reveal important information about the data.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777095826509813*^9, 3.777096010177582*^9}, {
  3.780145710190626*^9, 
  3.780145710197259*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"00429c7c-135e-4c1d-927e-\
bb0a5f08686d"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
 However, in other cases, it is the result of bad data, due to wrong physical \
conversion, or due to a malfunctioning sensor. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777095826509813*^9, 3.777096010177582*^9}, {
  3.780145714217872*^9, 
  3.7801457142230043`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4a4d496b-e9c4-4520-9fa5-\
2aaf937cb047"],

Cell["\<\
In such cases, the mean, median, trimmed or weighted mean are good estimators \
of location. Detection can be done by simply noticing data points that differ \
too much from these quantities.  \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777095826509813*^9, 3.777096010177582*^9}, {
  3.844662395844858*^9, 3.84466239979296*^9}, {3.884857742452922*^9, 
  3.884857766651494*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"877a857e-05dd-4a7c-b385-\
7fbb970e2e59"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

