    "], {{0, 284.}, {300., 0}}, {0, 255},
    ColorFunction->RGBColor,
    ImageResolution->72],
   BoxForm`ImageTag["Byte", ColorSpace -> "RGB", Interleaving -> True],
   Selectable->False],
  DefaultBaseStyle->"ImageGraphics",
  ImageSize->{452.8505401611328, Automatic},
  ImageSizeRaw->{300., 284.},
  PlotRange->{{0, 300.}, {0, 284.}}]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844669861195559*^9, 
  3.844669896346857*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3e70749d-e528-4e10-90dd-\
ab1dcca4ac98"],

Cell["\<\
A Spearman correlation of 1 results when the two variables being compared are \
monotonically related, ordinal, ranked, or non-normally distributed \
continuous data, even if their relationship is not linear. This means that \
all data points with greater x values than that of a given data point will \
have greater y values as well .\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844669889270213*^9, 3.844669890864648*^9}, {
  3.979123648475095*^9, 
  3.979123661116612*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8e1a8c4d-1005-4e98-9052-\
ab87246ba3aa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "From ",
 ButtonBox["Wikipedia",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spearman%27s_rank_correlation_\
coefficient"], None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spearman%27s_rank_correlation_coefficient"],\

 ", for example to access relationship between  IQ of a person with the \
number of hours spent in front of TV per week. "
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844669734452705*^9, 3.844669737612692*^9}, {
  3.844669773039007*^9, 3.844669796316043*^9}, {3.844669923978752*^9, 
  3.844670026441473*^9}, {3.979123605373254*^9, 
  3.979123605384408*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9e416b08-ce10-44fc-921c-\
e1a8963f6a5a"],

Cell["\<\
Investigating if higher ranks in hours spent revising correlate with higher \
ranks in final exam grades.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844669734452705*^9, 3.844669737612692*^9}, {
   3.844669773039007*^9, 3.844669796316043*^9}, {3.844669923978752*^9, 
   3.844670026441473*^9}, 
   3.979123605788513*^9},ExpressionUUID->"7b581dc8-500b-451c-b2f7-\
b368e48e518d"],

Cell["\<\
Or to access the relationship between being or not Covid19 positive with the \
number of hours travelled each day by bus.   \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844669734452705*^9, 3.844669737612692*^9}, {
  3.844669773039007*^9, 3.844669796316043*^9}, {3.844669923978752*^9, 
  3.844670026102624*^9}, {3.9791234832563877`*^9, 
  3.979123485158498*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a5eea7e4-7578-48a1-9bce-\
1f1bca9efdc5"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"c33ee5b0-1e33-4d07-b4a0-b3c6cc4908e7"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Nonlinear analysis for establishing relationship and causality, based on \
information\
\>", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844668350943283*^9, 3.844668370664241*^9}, {
  3.844669275825611*^9, 
  3.844669277958358*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f7f644cf-cb25-4e76-afe2-\
f77fd08cb853"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Correlation",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 " is not causation!"
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8446683748033867`*^9, 3.84466840809504*^9}, {
  3.8446684488546267`*^9, 
  3.844668452702005*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"644732f8-6508-450d-9404-\
431ed8f15217"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Mutual Information",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 " : measures how much information is shared between two time - series or \
data sets, X and Y. "
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8446683748033867`*^9, 3.84466840809504*^9}, {
  3.8446684488546267`*^9, 
  3.8446684687746*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a76f7efd-bbfc-466a-8f54-1fd76fc006dd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Transfer Entropy",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 ": measures the flux of information from the past of a variable X to the \
future of a Variable Y. If it is positive, variable X causes the future of \
variable Y. "
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8446683748033867`*^9, 
  3.844668441094263*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0317ad0b-5032-4079-8a37-\
cae999c70c90"],

Cell["\<\
This is out of the scope of this course, but my main area of research. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.844668482808391*^9, 3.844668538164414*^9}, {
  3.844668824737845*^9, 
  3.8446688264899187`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"cfa43b5b-9892-4113-8741-\
33ae46153b27"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.811249764561572*^9, 3.811249764951567*^9}},
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"60186145-5258-4660-a10d-644418c0ecbb"],

Cell["Network inference with correlation", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7771871990655813`*^9, 3.7771872547432632`*^9}, {
  3.844770848716917*^9, 
  3.8447708503538513`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b4d608bb-c3aa-4134-be38-\
9452898662a6"],

Cell["\<\
Correlation is an excellent tool to determine linear relationships between \
data or time - series:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7771872578446016`*^9, 3.777187326051713*^9}, 
   3.77718746959966*^9, {3.8446688511957073`*^9, 
   3.844668859254575*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4825ae57-66ff-4a49-a089-\
d1fad1d873e2"],

Cell["\<\
When modelling real world problems, the understanding between structure and \
behaviour is fundamental. \
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777187330002329*^9, 
  3.777187476545928*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d4d95083-1c50-4938-a2a0-\
426dd6e5f7ff"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["The reason is that sometimes, ", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777187330002329*^9, 
  3.7771875119172697`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1359996a-972a-4be5-b8f4-\
d093f9059c87"],

Cell["\<\
one has full or partial knowledge of the structural configurations of a \
system, and wants to predict its behaviour (e.g. the power grid, transport \
systems, flow networks, etc)\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777187330002329*^9, 3.7771875531545277`*^9}, {
  3.777187600453151*^9, 
  3.7771876186454296`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6d3845e1-c8cf-4c11-8547-\
1ea804e45ae7"],

Cell["\<\
one has  full or partial knowledge of the behaviour, but wants to determine \
its structure (e.g. inference of topology for the brain, socio-economic \
systems, stock market, etc)\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777187330002329*^9, 3.777187597503004*^9}, {
  3.979123894730281*^9, 3.979123894737259*^9}, {3.97912394770189*^9, 
  3.9791239477067137`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"e448b28a-6bc6-4616-8ca1-\
e60e5a6a8e1f"],

Cell["\<\
You can identify variables that provide similar information and drop \
redundant ones, which speeds up computation and simplifies models. \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777187330002329*^9, 3.777187597503004*^9}, {
   3.979123894730281*^9, 3.979123894737259*^9}, 
   3.9791239478159523`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"80da04db-d17f-4300-92c9-\
f9ead5b7fcc9"],

Cell["\<\
Understanding which variables are highly correlated with the target variable \
(and with each other) helps in selecting the most relevant features. \
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777187330002329*^9, 3.777187597503004*^9}, 
   3.979123894988249*^9, {3.9791239264084473`*^9, 
   3.979123926414645*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5c6ae22e-b231-4671-9b98-\
0bbfe1299f7e"],

Cell["\<\
Knowing how variables relate, such as how increased advertising spend \
correlates with sales, allows for better, data-driven decisions rather than \
relying on intuition.\
\>", "Subitem",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777187330002329*^9, 3.777187597503004*^9}, 
   3.979123894988249*^9, 
   3.979123926496574*^9},ExpressionUUID->"8886bc01-ecbb-4061-b2a0-\
3647f2fef555"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"f2ffefaf-b29f-4b4b-8ae2-3a1746611283"],

Cell["Some concepts in Network Science", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777188690254374*^9, 
  3.77718870047454*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9a033540-16ed-4fab-a3a9-\
78a59792ebbd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Adjacency Matrix ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " :\n  \n  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["A",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], "ij"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3bcb6c34-50c3-480b-ab7c-97c079b1341e"],
 " = 1, if node i sends connection to node j\n  \t0,  if node i is NOT \
connected to j"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777188702829914*^9, 3.777188727528914*^9}, {
  3.777189103579305*^9, 3.777189121670323*^9}, {3.77718915269407*^9, 
  3.777189201781355*^9}, {3.78030977004458*^9, 3.780309781135138*^9}, {
  3.979123982241531*^9, 
  3.97912398358263*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"952fdcea-11d6-4e04-985a-\
3a2f79b4f79b"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Out", " ", "Degree", " ", "to", " ", "node", " ", 
   RowBox[{"i", ":", " ", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    SubscriptBox["d", "i"]}]}], "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{
   UnderoverscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    RowBox[{"j", "=", "1"}], "N"], 
   SubscriptBox["A", "ij"]}]}]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777189215373887*^9, 3.77718922032517*^9}, {
  3.777189301102911*^9, 3.777189303936151*^9}, {3.777192932498948*^9, 
  3.777192966857092*^9}, {3.777193147277594*^9, 3.777193183450039*^9}, {
  3.780309804859389*^9, 
  3.780309811959268*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"267e233d-58cb-43d8-b486-\
8d972ba67ed2"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
