Cell["The receiver operating characteristic (ROC) curve ", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777195919239657*^9, 
  3.777195949258425*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"21f1fe22-d826-467a-b36c-\
bb74277532c9"],

Cell["\<\
The ROC curve is a graphical plot that illustrates the diagnostic ability of \
a binary classifier system as its discrimination threshold is varied.\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777195917207721*^9, 
  3.7771959606952147`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a54c0f3f-fb05-48b0-8723-\
1f14a5ccf78e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ROC curve can be created by plotting the ",
 StyleBox["true positive rate (TPR) ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "against the ",
 StyleBox["false positive rate (FPR), ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " at various threshold settings for the model."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.777195917207721*^9, 3.777195977609866*^9}, {
  3.780158441488038*^9, 3.78015844179699*^9}, {3.780161413988475*^9, 
  3.780161429886077*^9}, {3.9494093390539093`*^9, 
  3.9494093710846786`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"f7d80df4-abd7-4237-a750-\
ef8ee337260f"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["", "SlideShowNavigationBar",
 CellTags->
  "SlideShowHeader",ExpressionUUID->"da3176ea-25f4-4641-8c3c-529840565d44"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\


Hands - on example to model real state price: The California data set \
\>", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.884949806454049*^9, 3.884949840569944*^9}, {
  3.88494991540783*^9, 3.884949921651355*^9}, {3.886599827756224*^9, 
  3.886599833683613*^9}, {3.9177655223901777`*^9, 3.917765525746676*^9}, {
  3.949480097817595*^9, 
  3.94948009867695*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"40a64a00-929d-4068-b4a9-\
ce11aa5bc677"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
containing 20, 640 observations with 9 features, uses data from the 1990 U . \
S . Census and was introduced in a 1997 publication: Pace, R. Kelley and \
Ronald Barry, Sparse Spatial Autoregressions, Statistics and Probability \
Letters, 33 (1997) 291-297.\
\>", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.886599835828568*^9, 3.886599863836098*^9}, {
  3.8866004443217683`*^9, 
  3.886600444991548*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c49482c2-add8-4938-bc20-\
b3192909a6f4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Downloaded from ",
 ButtonBox["Kaggle",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/camnugent/california-housing-prices"]\
, None},
  ButtonNote->
   "https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/camnugent/california-housing-prices"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.886600448416127*^9, 
  3.88660047083301*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"87654e78-8097-4cc7-b8ba-\
8ea9a0cba475"],

Cell["\<\
Original dataset : https : // www . dcc . fc . up . \
pt/~ltorgo/Regression/cal_housing . html\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.886602537948469*^9, 
  3.886602544221408*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"544607f3-9eb1-4f82-84de-\
1c5f587c79a7"],

Cell["\<\
This dataset was derived from the 1990 U . S . census, using one row per census
block group . A block group is the smallest geographical unit for which the U \
. S . Census Bureau publishes sample data (a block group typically has a \
population of 600 to 3, 000 people) . 

A household is a group of people residing within a home. Since the average \
number of rooms and bedrooms in this dataset are provided per household, \
these columns may take surprisingly large values for block groups with few \
households and many empty houses, such as vacation resorts.

Median income for households within a block of houses is measured in tens of \
thousands of US Dollars (US$ 10,000), and Median House Value is measured in \
US Dollars
\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.886602579883816*^9, 3.8866025816073728`*^9}, {
   3.88660263246686*^9, 3.886602644664611*^9}, {3.887297159233673*^9, 
   3.887297173623725*^9}, 3.949409474319659*^9, {3.949412693267824*^9, 
   3.949412695540742*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"40d240b2-a0f3-4ce7-a6fd-\
53f1ce27df9c"],

Cell["\<\
More explanation : https : // inria . github . io/scikit - learn - \
mooc/python_scripts/datasets_california _housing . html\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.886602585010122*^9, 
  3.886602597427774*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5e677220-dd5f-45da-9337-\
ec781d084375"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

